Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Full Stack Engineer* role with *Thatch*. I bring over three years of professional experience building and shipping production web applications across the full stack, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my engineering roles, I have owned product flows end-to-end in ways that directly reflect the activation and engagement focus this position demands. At Sperse, I instrumented end-to-end product surfaces by building an MCP AI interaction layer that translates natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and full user behavior observability. I built full stack generative code solutions to accelerate developer onboarding and enrollment flows, and architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph to coordinate complex engagement and conversion workflows. To keep these systems production-ready, I implemented a full observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith covering tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks — reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50% through targeted concurrency and routing optimizations. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications — owning full stack features from backend services to user-facing interfaces. I also developed backend lifecycle workflows using AWS Step Functions to handle long-running data import jobs and improve activation reliability for onboarding pipelines. Together, these roles have prepared me to own and iterate on core product flows — from account creation through enrollment — and drive measurable impact on how customers experience a product.

My experience spans the instrumentation and data side of product engineering as well. I have built systems with structured observability from the ground up, designed to surface user behavior and identify opportunities for improvement — directly mirroring Thatch's need to instrument product surfaces and use data to inform decisions. I am comfortable working through ambiguity, partnering closely with product and design, and shipping changes that move conversion metrics. I value clarity over ceremony and quality over shortcuts, which aligns closely with how Thatch operates.

I have always been passionate about employee empowerment and making healthcare accessible and portable — the belief that employees should choose the coverage that's right for them and keep it from job to job. I would love to contribute my full stack engineering experience to furthering Thatch's mission of building a healthcare system people love. I would be glad to discuss my interest in this role further and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration — I look forward to connecting!

